text: Joachim Dahl (28 June 1892 - 31 July 1972) was a Norwegian politician for the Labour Party. He was elected to the Norwegian Parliament from Bergen in 1945, and was re-elected on one occasion. Dahl was born in Bergen and a member of Bergen city council from 1934 to 1940 and 1945 to 1946. ==References== * Category:1892 births Category:1972 deaths Category:Labour Party (Norway) politicians Category:Members of the Storting Category:20th-century Norwegian politicians
